## Linear Algebra Progression (current focus)

**Tier 1 — Fundamentals** (current): add, subtract, scalar multiply, Hadamard, transpose, dot, matrix-vector multiply, naive GEMM, trace/norms

**Tier 2 — Performance**: tiled GEMM, AVX-512 FMA kernel, cache-oblivious GEMM, Strassen

**Tier 3 — Decompositions**: LU, Cholesky, Householder QR, SVD, rank-revealing QR

**Tier 4 — Eigenvalues + Iterative**: power/inverse/Rayleigh iteration, Conjugate Gradient, Arnoldi

**Tier 5 — GPU**: tiled SGEMM kernel, cuBLAS dispatch, batched inversion, cuSPARSE

## Hardware Assumptions (dev machine)

- Ryzen 7 9800X3D: AVX-512, 96 MB 3D V-Cache — tile sizes can be larger than standard advice
- RTX 3060 12 GB: SM 8.6, 28 SMs — default launch: 256 threads/block
- Arch Linux, GCC 16 / Clang 22, Python 3.14
